summary: |
  Wave 3 ships /loom-roadmap status as a pure read over state.toon, a
  reusable digest renderer (buildDigest + renderDigest), and resume-delegate
  for /loom-resume dual-state ordering. digest.ts is I/O-free; a grep guard
  test asserts zero write primitives. resume-delegate.ts orders pipeline-state
  and roadmap-converge state by mtime, most-recently-modified first.

keyDecisions[3]:
  digest.ts kept I/O-free; readState lives in state-io.ts so digest module is trivially testable and provably pure
  Purity enforced via grep guard test (digest-purity.test.ts) that scans digest.ts for fs write primitives
  Dual-state resume ordering uses mtime descending — recent state wins regardless of which pipeline produced it

nextStageHints[3]:
  Phase 4 (multi-roadmap) plumbs --roadmap path through status; slug-derived paths feed digest builder
  Phase 6 (/loom-resume integration) wires resume-delegate.ts into the resume command
  --all CLI runner is described in status.md but a CLI entrypoint script may need wiring in Phase 6

